The manual is the best place to start.  It discusses important detail 
such as how your processor is recognized by Heritrix. 

Then, there are three writer processors in Heritrix at the moment.  I&#39;d 
suggest that you next try studying how these work.  If you want to 
maintain a pool of writers, study the ARC and experimental WARC 
writers.  See how they have common heritage 
(http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/io/ArchiveReaderFactory.html).  
Otherwise, checkout the MirrorWriter.

Regards specifying a datasource, I&#39;d imagine you&#39;d add a configuration 
that shows in the Heritrix UI that allows the user to type in a JDBC URL.

St.Ack


